oai_dc:dc.dc:title: First woman physician at City Hospital
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: City Hospital; Kane, Elizabeth C.; medicine; women; 1900s;
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: "50 YEARS AGO - April 15, 1903 - For the first time in history a woman physician is to be elected a member of the staff of the City Hospital, according to informed sources at the city hall. The woman physician is Dr. Elizabeth C. Kane, who has been practicing medicine for several years here."
